==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Yoruba'''

# '''Yorùbá''' (in Yoruba orthography) is a sub-[[w:Sahara|Saharan]] language. It belongs to the [[w:Benue-Congo|Benue-Congo]] branch of the [[w:Niger-Congo languages|Niger-Congo]] language family, and has nearly 30 million speakers in [[Nigeria]], [[Benin]], [[Togo]] and [[Sierra Leone]], as well as communities in [[Brazil]] and [[Cuba]].

